{
  "texts": [
    "This includes differential, linear, integral, and algebraic cryptanalysis [114,115], respectively.",
    "Differential cryptanalysis compares inputs to higher-order, truncated, impossible, and boomerang types.",
    "Plaintext, ci-phertext, and key are approximated linearly using the piling-up lemma (Matsui's invention).",
    "S-P-N block ciphers with substitution-permutation networks benefit from integral cryptanalysis.",
    "A square attack and a saturation attack are also documented."
  ]
}